ce:section.ce:para:
The optimized geometries of the investigated nanocomposite (GQD-PXIII) and doped nanocomposite (Os-GQD-PXIII) at PCM/CAM-B3LYP with 6–31 +G(d,p) and LANL2DZ in water are depicted in Fig. 2. The PXIII dye has three carboxylic groups (COOHs). Usually, and as mentioned in Section 1, the attachment of natural dye molecule to the GQD is performed by introducing an amide group (

                                 Image 1
                              ). The amid group acted as a linkage in which its carbon atom is attached to one of the carbons of GQD and its nitrogen atom is attached to some atom in the natural dye. In PXIII dye, there is no need to introduce the amide linkage between PXIII and GQD. Since the attachment between the two molecules can be attained by one of the PXIII’s carboxylic groups. Therefore, one of the carboxylic groups in PXIII was deprotonated, and two oxygen atoms were attached to two carbon atoms on GQD.
